editorialSummary.text: No-fuss Brazilian home cooking (fried plantains, empanadas, meats) in a casual, intimate space.

originalText.text:
First time here! Definitely coming back! Great food, great service, nice atmosphere. Keep in mind the restaurant is very small. 1 thing we didn't like is going to the bathroom. It's located in the kitchen.
The Caipirinha was absolutely delicious. Steak with shrimps outstanding, huge serving. Great for two. Beef stew was delicious along with Shrimp Stroganoff. Tasty avocado salad! The beans were prepared just right, very delicious.  Definitely try this place!

originalText.text: Local Brazilian restaurant in Hell‚Äôs Kitchen with a happy hr caipirinha special. I used to come here every week when I worked in the area. I decided to randomly give them a visit on a Friday afternoon. Food was fairly mediocre, I remember it being better. I ordered the pork chop. The sauce was great, but the meat itself was dry and tough. In the past the waiter would always ask if I want yellow or white rice, I didn‚Äôt get that option this time (I generally dislike white rice). Nor was I asked about the type of beans I wanted. I think this waiter is new. I asked for a caipirinha with just a little bit of sugar and it came extremely sweet, but I drank it. Then, when I ordered another round I emphasized that I would like just a small amount of sugar and it finally came that way. Not sure if I‚Äôd return very soon, but I like the ambiance. The bathroom situation is also a little annoying. You need to ask and wait because you need to walk through the actual kitchen. I usually order the chicken Milanese and it‚Äôs great, well-seasoned and fresh. Maybe I‚Äôd try that if I return.
